<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="510" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1567,1989]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1639,1664]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Butler, 1876" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1876" box="[327,705,1639,1664]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudosphenoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[327,548,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">Pseudosphenoptera</emphasis>
Butler, 
<number box="[649,705,1639,1664]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" value="1876.0">1876</number>
</taxonomicName>
is a genus with incredible dimorphism sexual, which can be attested by the existence of four generic synonyms for a total of six species that are currently placed in it. The males are considerably smaller than the females, and have more hyaline areas on the wings. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudosphenoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">Pseudosphenoptera boyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably no exception, though the female is unknown, and correct association might require finding moths copulating, or perhaps 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" box="[409,470,1784,1808]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" name="Department of Natural Resources, Environment, The Arts and Sport" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">DNA</collectionCode>
barcoding. To our knowledge the species is still known only from its 
<typeStatus box="[1257,1359,1783,1808]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">holotype</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Zerny" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" refString="Zerny, H. (1931 a) Ergebnisse einer zoologischen Sammelreise nach Brasilien, insbesondere in das Amazonasgebiet, ausgefuhrt von Dr. H. Zerny. VII. Teil. Lepidoptera III: Die Syntomiden des Staates Para. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 45, 225 - 263." type="journal article" year="1931" yearSuffix="a">
Zerny (
<number box="[159,216,1820,1844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" value="1931.0">1931</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
considered it close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hampson, 1914" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1914" box="[497,1018,1820,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Haematerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nephelophora">
<emphasis box="[497,809,1820,1845]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">Haematerion nephelophora</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson" box="[825,1009,1820,1844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1914) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, Supplement. vol. I. Catalogue of the Amatidae and Arctiadae (Nolinae and Lithosianae) in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, 858 pp." type="book" year="1914">
Hampson, 
<number box="[949,1009,1820,1844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" value="1914.0">1914</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, it also appears close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1854" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudosphenoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">P. basalis</emphasis>
(Walker, 
<number box="[341,401,1855,1880]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" value="1854.0">1854</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[462,510,1856,1880]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<emphasis box="[638,865,1855,1880]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">
<taxonomicName box="[638,862,1855,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudosphenoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudosphenoptera</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
meaning that 
<taxonomicName box="[1027,1217,1855,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Haematerion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nephelophora">
<emphasis box="[1027,1217,1855,1880]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">H. nephelophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is likely misplaced in 
<emphasis box="[180,328,1893,1916]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">Haematerion</emphasis>
Herrich-Schäffer, [
<number box="[544,607,1892,1917]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" value="1855.0">1855</number>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1567,1989]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName box="[426,474,1927,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pseudosphenoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boyi">
<emphasis box="[426,474,1927,1952]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="510">boyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
derives from the holotype’s collector, Hugo Charles Boy (
<number box="[1129,1260,1928,1952]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" value="1913.5" valueMax="1937.0" valueMin="1890.0">
<date box="[1129,1260,1928,1952]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" value="1890" valueMax="1937">1890–1937</date>
</number>
), who collected in the Brazilian and Peruvian Amazon in the 
<number box="[656,714,1964,1988]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" value="1920.0">1920</number>
s (
<bibRefCitation author="Lamas" box="[738,880,1964,1988]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" refString="Lamas, G. (1980) Historia de la Entomologia en el Peru. II. Periodo de los viajeros, colectores y estudiosos especializados. Revista Peruana de Entomologia, 23 (1), 25 - 31." type="journal article" year="1980">
Lamas 
<number box="[821,880,1964,1988]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Papavero" box="[891,1174,1964,1989]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" refString="Papavero, N. &amp; Overal, W. L. (2011) Taperinha: historico das pesquisas de historia natural realizadas em uma fazenda da regiao de Santarem, no Para, nos seculos XIX e XX. Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi, Belem, 460 pp." type="book" year="2011">
Papavero &amp; Overal 
<number box="[1114,1174,1964,1988]" pageId="5" pageNumber="510" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
